      "type": "verse",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You had one friend who betrayed You,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With a kiss, to hate-filled men,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And another who denied You"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Out of fear towards all of them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When they took You as their prisoner,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Questioned You, their anger bitter,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And then mocked You, thought a sinner,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You did not Yourself defend."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You were mute and long-enduring"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With a view to reach Your end."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The Sanhedrin sought to weaken"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Your endurance and Your strength,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Then delivered You to Pilate"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Whose men scourged You, whipped at length."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "At Golgotha, soldiers stripped You,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And with violent pounding nailed You"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To Your cross, through joint and sinew,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "There to hang upon the tree,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Where bystanders mocked, despising,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Wagging heads contempt’ously."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Those who hated You were staring,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "No respect, their visage hard."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Soldiers gambled for Your garments"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "While Your strength dried like a shard."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Like hot wax, Your heart was melting."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Gravity each joint was rending."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In Your mouth, Your tongue was cleaving."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As Your weight each breath then stole,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Your ordeal made all the harder"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When God made You sin for all."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "At the noon hour, when God judged You,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Laid on You the whole of sin,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "God’s dear presence fled, departed,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "From Your fellowship within."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "This was much worse than the violence;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "This forsaking—dreaded silence,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "All the scorn of men’s derision"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Paling in comparison"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To the scope of God’s own judgement"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Poured upon His only Son."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "After three hours, at Your limit,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You cried out in agony,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In the words of David, Psalmist,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“Why have You forsaken Me?”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Saying, “I thirst... It is finished”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You were done, Your work unblemished."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You prayed “Father, into Your hands"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I commit My spirit.” Then"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With a loud cry, You expired,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As Your loved ones grieved again."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When Your death the soldiers noticed,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "One took up His weighted spear"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And he pierced Your side in coldness,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Blood and water flowing clear."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "From Gethsemane to Calvary"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You were broken, suffering greatly."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Wounds innumerable, a fountain,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Flowing precious priceless blood,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For our sins and our redemption,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Reconciling us to God."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Lord, I praise You and I thank You"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That You bled and died for me,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As I ponder how You loved me"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And You gave Yourself for me."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I am filled with love and reverence,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Gratitude and deep assurance"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You forgive me in Your mercy,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "By Your blood, for all my sin!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And You joined me to the Father!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Hallelujah, Lord! Amen!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "8"
    }
  ],
